Job description 7 : 
Conduct user research through surveys, interviews, and usability tests to gain a deep understanding of user needs and requirements. 
Use insights to take informed design decisions and improve user experience.
● UI/UX Design:
Create high-quality wireframes, mockups, prototypes, and user flows that effectively communicate design
concepts. Ensure that designs are aligned with the company’s brand and user experience standards.
● Collaboration:
Work closely with product managers and developers to understand project goals, constraints, and requirements. 
Collaborate throughout the product development lifecycle to ensure designs are implemented as intended.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 8 : 
Interaction Design:

Design intuitive interactions and animations that enhance the user experience across various platforms (web, mobile, etc.).
Usability Testing & Iteration:
Conduct usability testing and gather feedback to refine designs. Iterate on designs based on data and user feedback to continuously improve the product.
Design Systems & Standards:
Contribute to the development and maintenance of the company’s design system, ensuring consistency
and scalability across products.
Proactive Problem-Solving:
Identify design challenges and propose innovative solutions. Stay up-to-date with design trends, tools, and best practices to continuously evolve your craft.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 9 : 
Core Responsibilities

1. Graphic Design

Craft compelling visual assets, including logos, banners, brochures, thumbnails, posters, and ads.
Ensure consistent brand identity across digital and print media.
Collaborate with marketing and product teams to visualize creative ideas.
2. Video Editing

Transform raw footage into engaging visual stories or marketing content.
Incorporate music, subtitles, transitions, and voiceovers.
Optimize videos for various platforms: YouTube, Instagram, TikTok, etc.
Handle color correction, grading, and audio balancing.​
3. Motion Graphics

Design animated intros, outros, lower thirds, transitions, infographics, and logo reveals.
Create explainer videos, product demos, and animated ads.
Utilize tools like After Effects, Blender, or Adobe Animate to enhance visual storytelling.
Collaborate with illustrators, designers, and writers to bring concepts to life.

