-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 12 : 
As a Product Designer, you will be responsible for defining and executing the product experience strategy, ensuring seamless alignment between user needs and business goals. 
You will lead design initiatives, collaborate with cross-functional teams, and craft innovative, user-centric solutions that enhance product usability and engagement.
Your role involves a blend of UX Research, Interaction Design, and Visual Design, driving end-to-end design solutions from concept to execution. 
By leveraging research, design thinking, and usability principles, you will play a critical role in shaping intuitive, transparent, and effective digital experiences that elevate user satisfaction and business success.
Travel for team and client meetings is required, typically up to 15%.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 13 : 
Participate in large scale design projects, ensuring high-quality execution aligned with product strategy and user needs.
Develop and deliver meaningful, user-centered design solutions, supported by comprehensive documentation for clear stakeholder communication.
Ensure design consistency by adhering to brand standards, usability best practices, and accessibility guidelines (WCAG).
Leverage research and usability testing to optimize product performance and enhance user experiences.
Work independently with minimal supervision, conducting peer reviews to maintain design quality.
Create and maintain a scalable Design System, supporting usability improvements and A/B testing with support of the leadership team.
Create user flows, wireframes, and prototypes that align with business goals and user needs to refine and enhance the user experience.
Iterate on designs based on feedback, demonstrating proficiency in Figma, Adobe CC, Sketch, and prototyping tools.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 14 : 
Collaborate with cross-functional teams (product managers, engineers, marketing) to define and implement innovative solutions for product direction and user experience.
Translate user needs and business goals into creative, functional designs.
Conduct user research, create user personas, and analyze user feedback to inform design decisions.
Develop wireframes, prototypes, and user flows to illustrate design concepts.
Create high-fidelity designs and detailed specifications for developers.
Ensure visual consistency and design quality across platforms (web, mobile, etc.).
Work closely with the engineering team to ensure accurate implementation of designs.
Iterate on designs based on feedback, testing, and analytics.
Stay up-to-date with latest design trends, tools, and technologies.
Present and defend design solutions to stakeholders and receive constructive feedback.
Lead and conduct user testing to validate design decisions.
Develop and maintain design systems, style guides, and design documentation.

